parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to serious injury or even death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Airbag does not deploy in the event of an accident
despite the severity of the impact.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the oil pump can cause engine damage, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing a collision, which can put the driver and others at risk.
symptoms: Engine light comes on
car engine revving up at stops
check engine light coming on
electrical malfunctions
and a decrease in engine power while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission faults can cause the vehicle to lose power, jerk, or slip, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents or damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: Error message "shift to park"
transmission jerking and slipping
difficulty accelerating
transmission jerking hard when taking foot off the gas pedal
and transmission fault codes (e.g. P0826 Shift up and down failure).

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering system can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Grinding noise when backing out
wobbling in front while driving on the highway
feeling like the back end of the vehicle is being pushed
and stalling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the safety restraint system can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Safety restraint system warning light comes on
seatbelt tensioner problem
and repeated failures despite multiple repairs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling and performance issues can cause accidents, injuries, and leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Engine light comes on and goes off
engine stalling
wobbling
and shaking
ticking noise
and electrical issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the infotainment system and electrical issues can cause distractions, accidents, and inconvenience.
symptoms: Headlights become inoperable
cell phone overheats when connected to Bluetooth
and Infotainment System failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Faulty Shift to Park Sensor or System
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty shift to park sensor or system can cause the vehicle to incorrectly indicate that it is not in park, leading to safety concerns such as the vehicle rolling away when exiting, and inconvenience to the driver.
symptoms: The vehicle displays an error message saying "shift to park" when the gearshift is already in park
the vehicle will not let the engine turn off
the vehicle indicates that it is not in park despite the dashboard indicator showing "P"
the driver is unable to turn off the engine
the driver is stuck in the vehicle for an extended period.
